<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Two people have been killed after their car ploughed into a tree in Sydney's south west on Sunday.  </p>

<p>Emergency services were called to Henry Lawson Drive near the Hume Highway in Lansdowne at 11pm. </p>

<p>Police have not revealed any information about the male driver or male passenger as they have not been formally identified.  </p>

<p>Pictured: Emergency services were called to Henry Lawson Drive near the Hume Highway in Lansdowne at 11pm</p>

<p>When emergency crews arrived, the two people inside the vehicle could not be saved</p>

<p>Authorities were called to the scene after witnesses described a Volkswagen Golf slamming into a tree. </p>

<p>The two people inside the vehicle could not be saved.</p>

<p>The crash closed Henry Lawson Drive in both directions for seven hours. </p>

<p>The busy thoroughfare between the Hume Highway and Milperra Road was re-opened at 6am on Monday. </p>

<p>Forensic officers from Bankstown Police are investigating the cause of the single-vehicle crash and will prepare a report for the coroner.</p>

<p>They have asked for anyone with dashcam footage of the incident to contact Bankstown Police station. </p>

<p> Police have not revealed any information about the male driver or male passenger as they have not been formally identified</p>

